et is on Post the Office Suite software can be installed on the computer  If you have purchased a laptop through Best Buy  Costco  Wal Mart  etc  and have purchased an extended warranty as well  the end user will need to contact the appropriate retailer for service  The operating system and Office Suite hereafter referred to as software  Software is made available to you because The Virginia Military Institute has purchased license coverage for the Software through Microsoft Campus Agreement Subscription Student Option  VMI is extending to you the right to use the Software on a personally owned computer or an institution owned computer designated for your exclusive use  You do not own the license  nor are you authorized to install the software on more than one computer  rather you are authorized to use the Software and any associated media pursuant to the terms and conditions of the license s  granted to VMI for the term of the Campus Agreement Subscription  You will be required to remove the Software from your personal machine immediately upon the earlier of  a  any event  with the exception of graduation  which causes you no longer to be a student of VMI or  b  expiration of the Campus Agreement Subscription term  If you graduate from VMI during the agreement period  the Software license will convert to a perpetual license  meaning you own the Software  as verified in your Student License Confirmation  The document is proof of Software ownership  You will need to obtain this license before leaving the Institute at graduation time  You are granted the right to use the following Software per the terms of the Campus Agreement Subscription Student Option  Microsoft Office does NOT come pre installed on the VMI recommended laptop  Dell Laptop Office 2010 Professional Edition  which includes  Word Excel PowerPoint Access Outlook Publisher    Apple Laptop Office 2011 for Mac which includes  Word Excel PowerPoint Outlook  I am currently  or have been accepted as  a cadet 